body:
# Prisma Client Queries

Complete reference for all CRUD operations, filters, and query options in [[prisma/client]].

## Read Operations

### findUnique â€” Find by unique field

```typescript
// By primary key
const user = await prisma.user.findUnique({ where: { id: 1 } });

// By unique field
const user = await prisma.user.findUnique({ where: { email: 'alice@example.com' } });

// By composite unique
const record = await prisma.post.findUnique({
  where: { authorId_slug: { authorId: 1, slug: 'my-post' } },
});

// Throws if not found
const user = await prisma.user.findUniqueOrThrow({ where: { id: 1 } });
```

### findFirst â€” Find first match

```typescript
const post = await prisma.post.findFirst({
  where: { published: true },
  orderBy: { createdAt: 'desc' },
});

// Throws if not found
const post = await prisma.post.findFirstOrThrow({ where: { published: true } });
```

### findMany â€” Find multiple records

```typescript
const users = await prisma.user.findMany({
  where: { role: 'ADMIN' },
  orderBy: { name: 'asc' },
  take: 10,
  skip: 0,
});
```

### count

```typescript
const total = await prisma.user.count();
const admins = await prisma.user.count({ where: { role: 'ADMIN' } });
```

### aggregate

```typescript
const stats = await prisma.product.aggregate({
  _avg: { price: true },
  _max: { price: true },
  _min: { price: true },
  _sum: { price: true },
  _count: true,
});
```

### groupBy

```typescript
const grouped = await prisma.user.groupBy({
  by: ['role'],
  _count: true,
  _avg: { age: true },
  having: { age: { _avg: { gt: 25 } } },
});
```

## Create Operations

```typescript
// Create one
const user = await prisma.user.create({
  data: {
    email: 'alice@example.com',
    name: 'Alice',
    role: 'ADMIN',
  },
});

// Create many
const result = await prisma.user.createMany({
  data: [
    { email: 'bob@example.com', name: 'Bob' },
    { email: 'charlie@example.com', name: 'Charlie' },
  ],
  skipDuplicates: true,  // Skip records with duplicate unique fields
});
// result.count = number of created records

// Create many and return (PostgreSQL, SQLite, CockroachDB)
const users = await prisma.user.createManyAndReturn({
  data: [{ email: 'a@b.com' }, { email: 'c@d.com' }],
});
```

## Update Operations

```typescript
// Update one (must match unique field)
const user = await prisma.user.update({
  where: { id: 1 },
  data: { name: 'Alice Updated' },
});

// Update many
const result = await prisma.user.updateMany({
  where: { role: 'USER' },
  data: { verified: true },
});

// Atomic number operations
const updated = await prisma.product.update({
  where: { id: 1 },
  data: {
    views: { increment: 1 },
    stock: { decrement: 1 },
    price: { multiply: 1.1 },
  },
});

// Upsert â€” update if exists, create if not
const user = await prisma.user.upsert({
  where: { email: 'alice@example.com' },
  update: { name: 'Alice Updated', lastLogin: new Date() },
  create: { email: 'alice@example.com', name: 'Alice' },
});
```

## Delete Operations

```typescript
// Delete one
const deleted = await prisma.user.delete({ where: { id: 1 } });

// Delete many
const result = await prisma.user.deleteMany({ where: { verified: false } });

// Delete all records in a table
const result = await prisma.user.deleteMany({});
```

## Filter Operators

### Comparison

```typescript
await prisma.user.findMany({
  where: {
    age: { gte: 18, lt: 65 },       // >= 18 AND < 65
    role: { not: 'ADMIN' },          // != ADMIN
    id: { in: [1, 2, 3] },           // IN (1, 2, 3)
    status: { notIn: ['BANNED'] },   // NOT IN
  },
});
```

### String Filters

```typescript
await prisma.user.findMany({
  where: {
    email: { contains: 'prisma', mode: 'insensitive' },
    name: { startsWith: 'A' },
    bio: { endsWith: '.' },
  },
});
```

### Compound Filters

```typescript
await prisma.user.findMany({
  where: {
    OR: [
      { email: { contains: 'admin' } },
      { role: 'ADMIN' },
    ],
    AND: [
      { verified: true },
      { age: { gte: 18 } },
    ],
    NOT: { status: 'BANNED' },
  },
});
```

### Null Checks

```typescript
await prisma.user.findMany({ where: { bio: null } });      // IS NULL
await prisma.user.findMany({ where: { bio: { not: null } } }); // IS NOT NULL
```

## Query Options

### select â€” Return specific fields

```typescript
const user = await prisma.user.findUnique({
  where: { id: 1 },
  select: { id: true, email: true, name: true },
});
// Type: { id: number; email: string; name: string | null }
```

### include â€” Load relations

```typescript
const user = await prisma.user.findUnique({
  where: { id: 1 },
  include: { posts: true, profile: true },
});
```

`select` and `include` cannot be used together at the same level.

### orderBy â€” Sort results

```typescript
await prisma.user.findMany({
  orderBy: [{ role: 'asc' }, { name: 'desc' }],
});

// Order by relation count
await prisma.user.findMany({
  orderBy: { posts: { _count: 'desc' } },
});
```

### Pagination

```typescript
// Offset pagination
await prisma.user.findMany({ skip: 20, take: 10 });

// Cursor pagination (more efficient for large datasets)
await prisma.user.findMany({
  take: 10,
  cursor: { id: lastSeenId },
  skip: 1,  // Skip the cursor record itself
});
```

### distinct â€” Unique values

```typescript
await prisma.user.findMany({
  distinct: ['role'],
  select: { role: true },
});
```
